 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Create a custom control in WPF for displaying temperature data."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Design, implement, style, and test a WPF custom control for temperature data display\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"UIDEVELOPER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Design TemperatureControl XAML\",\"description\":\"Create a new UserControl named TemperatureControl.xaml that includes a TextBlock to display the temperature and an optional Slider for adjusting the temperature.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement TemperatureControl.cs\",\"description\":\"Write the code behind for TemperatureControl.cs, which should include properties for Temperature (double) and methods for updating the UI when the temperature changes.\"},{\"role\":\"UIDEVELOPER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Style TemperatureControl\",\"description\":\"Create a ResourceDictionary named TemperatureControlStyles.xaml to define styles and templates for the TemperatureControl, ensuring it visually represents temperature data effectively.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify TemperatureControl Functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the TemperatureControl in a sample WPF application to ensure that it accurately displays and updates the temperature based on property changes.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "norm