 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Develop a logging system for the WPF desktop application."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Choose a logging library, implement a service to manage logs, integrate it into the WPF application, and test its functionality\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research Logging Libraries\",\"description\":\"Explore available logging libraries compatible with WPF applications, such as NLog or Serilog, and assess their features and ease of integration.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement Logger Service\",\"description\":\"Create a LoggerService.cs file to encapsulate the logging logic using the chosen library. The service should support different log levels (e.g., Info, Warning, Error).\"},{\"role\":\"UIDEVELOPER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Integrate Logger in Application\",\"description\":\"Modify MainWindow.xaml and related files to include a logging window or area where logs can be displayed for debugging purposes.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Logging Functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the application thoroughly to ensure that all log messages are generated and displayed correctly at various log levels. Check edge cases, such as logging during initialization or under heavy load.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "no