 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Design a data processing pipeline that imports, cleans, and exports CSV files efficiently."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Design a data processing pipeline using Python's pandas library for efficient CSV file import, cleaning, and export\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Analyze CSV File Formats\",\"description\":\"Identify common formats, delimiters, and potential issues in CSV data to ensure robust handling.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Develop Import Service\",\"description\":\"Create a service (e.g., Services/CsvImportService.cs) that reads and parses CSV files into a common data model.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement Data Cleaning Logic\",\"description\":\"Write code in the DataProcessingService.cs file to clean and validate the imported data, handling missing values, duplicates, and errors.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Develop Export Service\",\"description\":\"Create a service (e.g., Services/CsvExportService.cs) that converts cleaned data back into CSV format for export.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T01:37:48", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 119. 