 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Create a simple PowerShell script for managing Windows services."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Develop a PowerShell script using conditional statements and cmdlets to manage Windows services, including start, stop, and restart functionalities\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create Service Management Script\",\"description\":\"Write a PowerShell script named 'ManageWindowsServices.ps1' that includes functions to start, stop, restart, and check the status of Windows services.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Start Functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the start function with a known service to ensure it correctly starts the service without errors.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Stop Functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the stop function with a known service to ensure it correctly stops the service without errors.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Restart Functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the restart function with a known service to ensure it correctly restarts the service without errors.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T01:43:45", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.