 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Develop a PowerShell script to monitor and log system performance metrics."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Identify key system performance metrics, create a PowerShell script to collect them, and test the script's accuracy\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Identify System Performance Metrics\",\"description\":\"Research common system performance metrics that should be monitored, such as CPU usage, memory usage, disk space, and network activity.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create PowerShell Script for Metric Collection\",\"description\":\"Write a PowerShell script named 'SystemPerformanceMonitor.ps1' to collect the identified metrics. The script should output the results in a readable format or export them to a log file.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Metric Collection\",\"description\":\"Run the PowerShell script on a test system and verify that it correctly collects and logs all specified performance metrics.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T01:45:02", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 136. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
