 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Develop a PowerShell script to monitor system resource usage."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Gather data using Get-Process and Get-Counter cmdlets, create a script to collect and display resource usage, then test the script's accuracy and reliability\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Gather System Resource Usage Data\",\"description\":\"Research the cmdlets and modules available in PowerShell that can be used to gather system resource usage data such as CPU, memory, disk, and network.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create ResourceUsageMonitor.ps1 Script\",\"description\":\"Develop a PowerShell script named ResourceUsageMonitor.ps1 that uses the gathered cmdlets to collect and display system resource usage data in a readable format.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Validate Script Functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the ResourceUsageMonitor.ps1 script on different systems to ensure it accurately collects and displays resource usage data without errors or performance issues.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T02:24:42", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 210. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
