 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Create a simple IoT device that communicates with a local server."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Conduct research on existing IoT protocols, implement device code using selected protocol, test communication with server, and design a user interface for configuration\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research Existing IoT Communication Protocols\",\"description\":\"Identify and research commonly used IoT communication protocols such as MQTT, CoAP, or HTTP for the project.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement IoT Device Code\",\"description\":\"Create a C# class library (e.g., IoTDeviceLibrary.cs) that encapsulates the logic for communicating with the local server using one of the researched protocols.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Communication Between IoT Device and Server\",\"description\":\"Simulate a local server and an IoT device to ensure they can communicate effectively using the chosen protocol.\"},{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Design User Interface for IoT Device Configuration\",\"description\":\"Create wireframes or mockups for a simple user interface that allows users to configure the IoT device's connection settings to the local server.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_