 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Document the process for updating firmware on multiple devices concurrently."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Conduct research on existing firmware protocols, design a scalable Firmware Update Service, and implement concurrent update testing\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Understand current firmware update protocols\",\"description\":\"Research existing firmware update protocols and standards used by the device manufacturer.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create Firmware Update Service\",\"description\":\"Develop a service (e.g., Services/FirmwareUpdateService.cs) that handles concurrent firmware updates. This service should manage connection pooling, queue management, and error handling.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify concurrent update functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the Firmware Update Service to ensure it can handle multiple devices updating at the same time without conflicts or errors.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T02:36:53", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 250. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
