 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Develop a data processing module that cleans and transforms CSV files for reporting."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Design a DataProcessor class with methods to clean and transform CSV data, then implement unit tests for each functionality\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create DataProcessor Class\",\"description\":\"Implement a class named DataProcessor in the file Services/DataProcessor.cs. The class should have methods for reading CSV files, cleaning data (e.g., removing duplicates, handling missing values), and transforming data (e.g., pivoting tables, aggregating data).\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Validate Data Cleaning Functionality\",\"description\":\"Verify that the DataProcessor class correctly cleans CSV data by using predefined test cases. Ensure that duplicates are removed and missing values are handled appropriately.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Validate Data Transformation Functionality\",\"description\":\"Check that the DataProcessor class accurately transforms CSV data according to specified rules, such as pivoting tables or aggregating columns.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T02:37:30", "notes": "Norm