 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: 27. Build a testing framework in PowerShell to test scripts and modules."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Identify Pester, set up basic testing framework, verify setup\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Identify existing PowerShell testing frameworks\",\"description\":\"Explore existing PowerShell testing frameworks like Pester, ShouldProcess, and NUnit for PowerShell.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Set up a basic testing framework using Pester\",\"description\":\"Create a new PowerShell script (e.g., TestFramework.ps1) to set up the basic structure of the Pester-based testing framework.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify initial setup and execution\",\"description\":\"Run the initial test framework to ensure it is correctly set up and that tests can be executed.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T03:08:28", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 309. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
