 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: 33. Build a testing plan for an IoT project to ensure all devices are communicating correctly."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Develop a comprehensive testing plan including device discovery, data integrity verification, latency assessment, and failover scenario simulation to ensure seamless communication in an IoT project\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Device Discovery and Connection Test\",\"description\":\"Verify that the system can discover and connect to all IoT devices on the network.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Data Integrity Check\",\"description\":\"Ensure that data transmitted between devices is accurate and not corrupted.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Latency Test\",\"description\":\"Measure the delay in communication to identify any performance bottlenecks.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Failover Scenario Test\",\"description\":\"Test how the system behaves when a device goes offline and re-connects.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T03:08:36", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 310. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
