 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: 41. Develop a PowerShell script that automates the backup of critical data files weekly on Saturdays."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Develop a PowerShell script to automate weekly backups of critical data files on Saturdays, test its execution, schedule it accordingly, and verify the scheduled runs\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create Backup Script\",\"description\":\"Write a PowerShell script named 'BackupCriticalData.ps1' in the 'C:\\\\Scripts' directory to automate the backup of critical data files.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Test Script Execution\",\"description\":\"Manually run the 'BackupCriticalData.ps1' script on a Saturday and verify that it correctly backs up the critical data files to the designated location.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Schedule Script Execution\",\"description\":\"Use Task Scheduler in Windows to set up the 'BackupCriticalData.ps1' script to run automatically every Saturday at a specified time.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Scheduled Execution\",\"description\":\"Wait for the next scheduled execution of the backup script and verify that it runs as expected, backing up the critical data files without errors.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_