 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Enhance the PowerShell script for backup to include versioning."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Integrate a timestamp-based naming convention in the PowerShell script to implement backup versioning\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research Backup Versioning Techniques\",\"description\":\"Explore existing backup tools and techniques that support versioning to understand best practices.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Modify PowerShell Script for Versioning\",\"description\":\"Update the existing PowerShell script located at Scripts/Backup.ps1 to include versioning functionality. Ensure each backup is stored with a timestamp or incrementing version number.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Backup Versioning\",\"description\":\"Test the modified PowerShell script to ensure that it correctly backs up files and creates separate versions for each backup operation.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T03:27:40", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 341. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
