 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: 33. Implement a new feature in the IoT device management system that allows remote access to camera feeds."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Integrate RESTful API with OAuth for secure camera feed access, develop CameraService.cs to handle requests, design user interface elements for viewing feeds, and test connectivity and authentication\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Review existing APIs and protocols for accessing IoT device cameras\",\"description\":\"Investigate current solutions and standards for remotely accessing camera feeds from IoT devices.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement CameraService.cs\",\"description\":\"Create a new service class named CameraService.cs that handles the logic for accessing and streaming camera feeds from IoT devices.\"},{\"role\":\"UIDEVELOPER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Design and implement camera feed viewer in the web interface\",\"description\":\"Develop a user interface component to display the camera feeds received from the CameraService.cs.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify remote access functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the ability to remotely access and view camera feeds from multiple IoT devices in various network conditions.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "norm