 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Implement error handling and logging in the PowerShell scripts."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Review scripts, create custom error handling, determine logging needs, implement and test\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Review existing PowerShell scripts\",\"description\":\"Examine all existing PowerShell scripts to understand their functionality, identify common error patterns, and gather requirements for consistent error handling and logging.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement custom error handling module\",\"description\":\"Create a new PowerShell module (e.g., ErrorHandling.psm1) that includes functions to handle errors gracefully, log them, and return user-friendly messages. Ensure the module can be easily imported into other scripts.\"},{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Determine logging requirements\",\"description\":\"Decide on the format of logs (e.g., JSON, CSV) and where they should be stored (e.g., local file, centralized log server). Review best practices for PowerShell script logging.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify error handling and logging implementation\",\"description\":\"Test the new error handling and logging module by intentionally causing errors in existing scripts and verifying that they are correctly logged and handled. Ensure that logs contain all necessary information for debugging and auditing.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": 