 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Implement real-time data streaming in the desktop app."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Integrate WebSocket for real-time communication, design a dynamic UI to display data in real-time, and test the system with various data streams\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research Real-Time Data Streaming Technologies\",\"description\":\"Explore existing technologies and libraries that support real-time data streaming in desktop applications, such as SignalR, gRPC, or RabbitMQ.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Set Up Real-Time Communication Layer\",\"description\":\"Integrate a chosen real-time communication library into the project. For example, if using SignalR, create a new file named 'RealTimeHub.cs' to handle real-time data streaming.\"},{\"role\":\"UIDEVELOPER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Design Real-Time Data Display Interface\",\"description\":\"Update the user interface to include components that can dynamically display incoming real-time data, such as charts or lists. Implement this in a file named 'RealTimeDataView.xaml' and its corresponding code-behind file 'RealTimeDataView.xaml.cs'.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Real-Time Data Streaming Functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the real-time data streaming feature to ensure it works as expected, with no delays or packet loss. Simulate various scenarios and validate that the UI updates in a timely manner.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning",