 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: 8. Create a PowerShell script to monitor disk space usage across all servers and alert if below threshold."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Develop a PowerShell script by researching existing solutions, implementing disk space monitoring logic, and testing it on multiple servers\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research existing PowerShell scripts for disk space monitoring\",\"description\":\"Search for publicly available PowerShell scripts that can monitor disk space usage on multiple servers.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create a PowerShell script to monitor disk space across all servers\",\"description\":\"Develop a PowerShell script named DiskSpaceMonitor.ps1 that iterates through a list of server names and checks the disk space usage. The script should alert if any drive is below a specified threshold.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Test the PowerShell script on a sample set of servers\",\"description\":\"Run the DiskSpaceMonitor.ps1 script on a small group of servers to ensure it correctly checks disk space and alerts when necessary.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T05:29:03", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_r