 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: 18. Refactor the data retrieval logic in our WPF app to use asynchronous programming."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Refactor data service to use async/await, update UI to display loading states, and implement unit tests for new async methods\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Investigate current data retrieval methods\",\"description\":\"Analyze existing synchronous data retrieval methods used in the WPF application.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Refactor data service to use asynchronous operations\",\"description\":\"Modify the DataService.cs file to implement asynchronous versions of data retrieval methods using async/await pattern.\"},{\"role\":\"UIDEVELOPER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Update UI to handle asynchronous data retrieval\",\"description\":\"Modify MainWindow.xaml.cs and other relevant view model files to handle asynchronous data loading without blocking the UI thread.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify asynchronous functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the application to ensure that data is retrieved asynchronously and that the UI remains responsive during data load operations.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2