 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: 29. Create a PowerShell script to automate the installation of software packages on multiple machines."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Research, then create and test a PowerShell script for automating software installations across multiple machines using a chosen package manager\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research available software package management tools\",\"description\":\"Identify and research popular software package management tools that can be used within PowerShell scripts for automating installations.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create a PowerShell script to automate installation\",\"description\":\"Develop a PowerShell script named 'InstallSoftware.ps1' that takes a list of machines and software packages as input, then installs the specified software on each machine.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify script functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the 'InstallSoftware.ps1' script with a small set of machines and software packages to ensure it functions as intended without errors.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T05:33:55", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 593. Plan gen