 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Implement an automated testing framework for the PowerShell automation scripts."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Research, develop, verify, and integrate a custom PowerShell testing framework\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research existing PowerShell testing frameworks\",\"description\":\"Identify and document current tools and techniques for testing PowerShell scripts, including their strengths and weaknesses.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Develop a base test class\",\"description\":\"Create a C# class library (e.g., `PowerShellTests/Tests/BaseTest.cs`) that includes common setup and teardown methods for PowerShell tests.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify the base test class works as expected\",\"description\":\"Run a few basic tests using the newly created base class to ensure it correctly handles PowerShell script execution and assertions.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Integrate the testing framework with an existing PowerShell project\",\"description\":\"Modify an existing PowerShell script project (e.g., `PowerShellScripts/MyScript.ps1`) to include unit tests using the developed test class.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", 