 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Refactor the login interface in C#/WPF to support multi-factor authentication."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Refactor C#/WPF login interface by integrating multi-factor authentication through research, design, implementation, and testing phases\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research Multi-Factor Authentication Methods\",\"description\":\"Gather information on common MFA methods such as SMS, Email, and Authenticator Apps.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement MFA Interface\",\"description\":\"Create a new UserMfaService.cs file to handle MFA logic. Implement necessary methods for sending verification codes and validating them.\"},{\"role\":\"UIDEVELOPER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Design MFA UI\",\"description\":\"Update the LoginWindow.xaml to include fields and controls for entering verification codes from different MFA methods.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Test MFA Implementation\",\"description\":\"Verify that MFA is working correctly by simulating login attempts with valid and invalid verification codes for different MFA methods.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T05:42:21", "notes": "Normalized from hardcore