 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Implement logging for all API requests in our data processing service."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Select a suitable logging framework, integrate it into the API layer, and test the implementation for accuracy\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Review existing logging frameworks\",\"description\":\"Identify and review the current logging framework used by the data processing service to ensure compatibility and performance.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement API request logging\",\"description\":\"Add middleware or filters in the ASP.NET Core pipeline to log all incoming API requests, including headers, body, and timestamps. Implement this in a new file: Middleware/ApiLoggingMiddleware.cs.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify logging functionality\",\"description\":\"Test various API endpoints to ensure that they are correctly logged with the expected information (headers, body, timestamp) and that logs are stored in the correct location.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T05:42:48", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 620. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
