 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Create a data processing pipeline that handles large CSV files without running out of memory."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Use a memory-efficient CSV library, implement a streaming parser service, and optimize data processing algorithms to handle large files without memory overflow\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Identify efficient CSV parsing libraries\",\"description\":\"Research and identify C# libraries for parsing large CSV files efficiently without consuming excessive memory.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create CSV parser service\",\"description\":\"Develop a service (e.g., Services/CsvParserService.cs) that uses an efficient library to parse large CSV files in chunks, processing each chunk individually.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Validate CSV parsing functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the CSV parser service with various-sized CSV files to ensure it handles them efficiently and accurately without memory overflow.\"},{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Optimize data processing logic\",\"description\":\"Research and identify optimization techniques for processing large datasets, such as parallel processing or distributed computing approaches if necessary.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T05:49:55", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 627. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
