 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Develop a C#/WPF desktop application for managing inventory tracking."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Develop a C#/WPF desktop application for inventory tracking by researching WPF and inventory management patterns, creating the MainWindow.xaml, implementing the InventoryItemViewModel.cs, and verifying functionality through testing\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research WPF and Inventory Management Patterns\",\"description\":\"Study existing WPF applications and inventory management patterns to understand best practices and technologies.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create MainWindow.xaml\",\"description\":\"Design the main window layout for the application, including controls for displaying inventory items, adding new items, and updating existing ones.\"},{\"role\":\"UIDEVELOPER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement InventoryItemViewModel.cs\",\"description\":\"Develop a ViewModel to manage the data and logic for individual inventory items, including properties for item name, quantity, and other relevant details.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Application Functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the application to ensure that adding, updating, and deleting inventory items works correctly and the user interface responds appropriately.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "