 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Develop an IoT device application in C# that reads temperature data from sensors every 5 minutes and stores it locally."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Develop a C# IoT app using .NET Core, integrate sensor protocols via libraries, implement a timer service for every 5-minute data reads, and use local storage solutions like JSON files or SQLite to save temperature data\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research IoT Sensor Protocols\",\"description\":\"Identify the protocols and libraries required to interface with the temperature sensors.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement Sensor Reading Service\",\"description\":\"Create a service class (e.g., Sensors/TempSensorService.cs) that reads temperature data from the sensors.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Develop Data Storage Logic\",\"description\":\"Write code to store the temperature readings locally in a database or file system (e.g., Services/DataStorageService.cs).\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Sensor Reading Functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the sensor reading service to ensure it correctly reads data from the sensors.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_genera