 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Develop an embedded system firmware that manages device settings over a serial connection."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Conduct research on serial protocols, implement a communication service, design a configuration screen, and test functionality\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research existing serial communication protocols\",\"description\":\"Investigate and document common serial communication protocols (e.g., RS-232, UART) that can be used for device settings management.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create a Serial Communication Service\",\"description\":\"Develop a C# class named 'SerialCommunicationService' in the file Services/SerialCommunicationService.cs. This service should handle opening, closing, and sending/receiving data over a serial port.\"},{\"role\":\"UIDEVELOPER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Design Serial Settings Configuration Screen\",\"description\":\"Create a new form or dialog named 'SerialSettingsForm' in the file UI/Forms/SerialSettingsForm.cs. This screen should allow users to configure serial settings such as baud rate, parity, and stop bits.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Serial Communication Functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the serial communication functionality by sending commands from the configuration screen and verifying that responses are received correctly. Ensure error handling is robust for connection issues.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T06:04:51", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 650. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
