 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Create a simple PowerShell script that monitors network traffic on specific ports and logs any unusual activity."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Develop a PowerShell script using the .NET System.Net.NetworkInformation namespace to monitor network traffic on specific ports and log unusual activity by capturing and analyzing packet data\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research Network Traffic Monitoring Tools\",\"description\":\"Gather information on existing tools and libraries that can be used for network traffic monitoring in PowerShell.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Develop Network Traffic Monitoring Script\",\"description\":\"Create a PowerShell script named 'MonitorNetworkTraffic.ps1' that listens on specific ports (e.g., 80, 443) and logs any unusual activity to a file.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Network Traffic Monitoring Script\",\"description\":\"Test the script by sending traffic on monitored ports and checking if the script correctly logs any unusual activity.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T06:06:15", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 653. Plan generated by qwen2.5-c