 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Implement data processing logic in a C# class to aggregate sales data from multiple CSV files."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Identify sales fields, create CSV reader, design aggregation service, test logic\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Identify required sales data fields\",\"description\":\"Determine the specific fields needed for aggregating sales data, such as date, product ID, quantity, and price.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create CSV file reader class\",\"description\":\"Develop a class to read sales data from individual CSV files. The class should be named 'CsvSalesDataReader.cs' and include methods for opening, reading, and parsing the data.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Design sales aggregation service\",\"description\":\"Create a service class to aggregate data from multiple CSV files into a single dataset. The class should be named 'SalesAggregationService.cs' and include methods for processing and summarizing the data.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify data aggregation logic\",\"description\":\"Test the sales aggregation service to ensure it correctly reads data from multiple CSV files, aggregates them accurately, and produces expected results.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "nor