 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Design an API client in PowerShell to interact with another service's RESTful endpoints."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Research and utilize existing PowerShell modules to create an API client script implementing basic HTTP methods for interacting with RESTful endpoints\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research existing PowerShell modules for HTTP requests\",\"description\":\"Investigate and document any existing PowerShell modules or libraries that can be used to make HTTP requests, such as Invoke-RestMethod.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create a new PowerShell script file\",\"description\":\"Generate a new PowerShell script file named `ApiClient.ps1` where the API client will be implemented.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement basic HTTP methods in the API client\",\"description\":\"In the `ApiClient.ps1` script, implement functions for GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE HTTP methods. Each function should accept parameters like URL, headers, and body (for POST/PUT).\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify API client functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the API client by making requests to a test endpoint and verifying that the responses are received correctly.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-12T23:18:01", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 671. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
