 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Refactor a legacy C# project to use modern .NET features."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Identify legacy features, migrate to modern C#, evaluate libraries, run tests\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Identify Legacy Features\",\"description\":\"Review the codebase to identify and document any legacy features or patterns that are not compatible with modern .NET.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Migrate to Modern C# Syntax\",\"description\":\"Refactor existing C# files (e.g., Controllers/AccountController.cs) to use the latest syntax and language features available in modern .NET, such as async/await, pattern matching, nullable references, etc.\"},{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Evaluate Third-Party Libraries\",\"description\":\"Assess any third-party libraries being used to determine if they have modern .NET equivalents or if updates are available.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Run Unit Tests and Integration Tests\",\"description\":\"Verify that the refactored code still passes all existing unit tests (e.g., Tests/UnitTests/UserServiceTests.cs) and integration tests (e.g., Tests/IntegrationTests/AccountControllerTests.cs).\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": 