 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Develop a simple data processing tool in C# that reads from a CSV file, processes the data, and outputs results."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Design a C# application with a CSVReader class for file input, a DataProcessor class for data manipulation, and unit tests to ensure functionality\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create CSVReader class\",\"description\":\"Implement a class named CSVReader.cs that includes a method to read data from a CSV file.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Develop DataProcessor class\",\"description\":\"Create a class named DataProcessor.cs with methods to process the data read by the CSVReader class.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify CSVReader functionality\",\"description\":\"Test the CSVReader class to ensure it correctly reads and parses the CSV file.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Validate DataProcessor logic\",\"description\":\"Check that the DataProcessor class processes the data as expected, including edge cases.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-12T23:25:01", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 743. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
