 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Create a data processing pipeline using C# that reads data from a CSV file, transforms it, and writes it to a SQL database."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Design a C# pipeline using classes for data models, CSV reading, transformation, and SQL writing\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Create DataModel.cs\",\"description\":\"Define the C# class representing the data structure in your CSV file.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Implement CSVReader.cs\",\"description\":\"Write a class to read data from a CSV file and map it to the DataModel objects.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Develop DataTransformer.cs\",\"description\":\"Create a service that transforms the DataModel objects into a format suitable for SQL database insertion.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Write SQLWriter.cs\",\"description\":\"Implement a class to insert the transformed data into a SQL database using appropriate ADO.NET commands.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-12T23:58:02", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 791. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b."}}
