 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Implement caching mechanisms in a C# WPF application to improve performance by reducing network calls."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Integrate MemoryCache with optimized policies in the WPF application to reduce network calls and improve performance\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Research Caching Mechanisms for .NET Applications\",\"description\":\"Explore popular caching libraries and techniques that can be used in a WPF application, such as MemoryCache or Redis.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Integrate MemoryCache into the Application\",\"description\":\"Implement MemoryCache to cache data retrieved from network calls. Create a CacheService.cs file with methods for adding, retrieving, and removing cached items.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"Verify Cache Implementation\",\"description\":\"Test the caching mechanism by simulating network calls and verifying that data is correctly cached and retrieved from cache instead of the network.\"},{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"Optimize Cache Policies\",\"description\":\"Research different cache policies such as sliding expiration, absolute expiration, and size-based eviction to determine the best strategy for your application.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by