 no preamble, no trailing text.\nString values MUST NOT contain literal newlines — use \\n inside strings if needed.\n{\n  \"plan\": \"one-sentence overall approach\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"RESEARCHER\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Short descriptive title\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed, self-contained instructions for this minion. Use \\n for line breaks inside this string.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Goal: Develop an API integration for integrating with an external API service."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\"plan\":\"Conduct research on the external API documentation, implement an API client using the identified methods, and thoroughly test the integration for functionality and performance\",\"tasks\":[{\"role\":\"RESEARCHER\",\"priority\":1,\"title\":\"External API Documentation Research\",\"description\":\"Gather and review the documentation of the external API service to understand its endpoints, request formats, authentication methods, and rate limits.\"},{\"role\":\"CODER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"API Client Implementation\",\"description\":\"Develop a new C# class (e.g., ExternalApiClient.cs) that handles communication with the external API, including making requests and handling responses.\"},{\"role\":\"TESTER\",\"priority\":2,\"title\":\"API Integration Testing\",\"description\":\"Verify that the API client can successfully make requests to the external service and handle various scenarios such as successful responses, errors, and edge cases.\"}]}"}], "metadata": {"category": "boss_planning", "task_type": "feature_plan", "source": "hardcorepc_normalized", "quality": "silver", "contains_sensitive_data": false, "base_model_target": "theorc-boss:gemma4", "created_by": "normalize_hardcorepc_boss.py", "original_model": "qwen2.5-coder:7b", "original_generated": "2026-06-13T00:13:45", "notes": "Normalized from hardcorepc_raw_overnight.jsonl example 816. Plan generated by qwen2.5-coder:7b.